<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                    <head>No. 392.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 21,
                            1883</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Morgan cables that he is informed by telegraph from our consul at
                        Mazatlan that Captain Caleb is sentenced to five years’ imprisonment, that
                        the Adriana is confiscated and the crew released, and that the case has been
                        appealed.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>